      "writtenOn": "2018-05-24T13:57:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m emulating what the Gerrit API does here.  CreateChange just creates a new empty Change. \n EditFile (Move, Delete, etc) and SetCommitMessage cause a ChangeEdit to be created on top of an existing Change.  The ChangeEdit does not become a patch set until Publish is run.\n\nIt didn\u0027t make sense to me to add these methods directly to the GerritInterface, because the act of creating a ChangeEdit is essentially a new context that needs to be managed (and finalized, either with Publish or Delete).  Personally, it makes more sense to me for some methods of GerritInterface to be moved to be methods of ChangeInfo, eg. SetReview, AddComment, SendToCQ, etc.",
      "parentUuid": "5526d194_0fe92bfa",
      "revId": "198251649310a9a5f4db04fdfabfa0dcac6d4536",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "64745a63_ea5335be",
        "filename": "go/gerrit/create_cl.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 21,
      "author": {
        "id": 5145
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-24T14:24:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "To me these are the 2 options-\n1) Either these methods should be moved to GerritInterface because it already has methods that deal with ChangeInfo. Some new methods should have a comment saying will not take effect until Publish/Delete or something like that.\n2) Move everything that deals with ChangeInfo in GerritInterface to be methods of ChangeInfo.\n\nRight now it seems to be in a fuzzy area between (1) and (2).\nI think it is easier to do (1) because the structure already exists. For (2) there are likely lots of callers and tests that will have to be updated.\n\nAlso things like EditFile/SetCommitMsg/Publish does not have to be tied to create_cl/create_change. Callers might want to do that for existing changes as well.",
      "parentUuid": "424b83fa_d436c238",
      "revId": "198251649310a9a5f4db04fdfabfa0dcac6d4536",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
